# Figma ↔ my-portfolio

When implementing from Figma or describing specs for Figma, use the same foundations as the live site.

## Color tokens (mirror in Figma as variables)

Source: `src/app/globals.css` `:root`.

| Token / role | CSS | Hex (reference) |
|--------------|-----|-----------------|
| Background | `--background` | `#0a0a0a` |
| Foreground | `--foreground` | `#fafafa` |
| Muted text | `--muted` | `#71717a` |
| Muted foreground | `--muted-foreground` | `#a1a1aa` |
| Border | `--border` | `#27272a` |
| Card | `--card` | `#141414` |
| Card hover | `--card-hover` | `#1a1a1a` |
| Accent | `--accent` | `#c9a227` |
| Accent tint | `--accent-muted` | `rgba(201, 162, 39, 0.15)` |
| Radius | `--radius` | `0.5rem` |

Tailwind maps these via `@theme inline` (e.g. `bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `text-accent`). Prefer semantic tokens over raw hex in code.

## Typography

From `src/app/layout.tsx`:

- Body / UI: **Geist Sans** (`--font-geist-sans`)
- Code / mono: **Geist Mono** (`--font-geist-mono`)
- Display / headings: **Syne** (`--font-syne`, weights 400–800)

In Figma, set matching text styles and use Syne for hero/display blocks.

## Page structure (section components)

Under `src/components/sections/`: `Hero`, `About`, `Skills`, `Services`, `FeaturedShowcase`, `Projects`, `Contact`. Layout: `Navbar`, `Footer`, `DotFieldBackground`.

When pulling Figma into code or pushing structure to Figma, keep this section order and naming where possible.

## Stack notes

- Next.js App Router; client components only where needed.
- Tailwind CSS v4 with `@import "tailwindcss"` and `@theme inline` in `globals.css`.
- Effects: `depth-section` class uses 3D-style perspective; dot field is animated in CSS (`dot-wander`).
